[b]Elliott Wave Radar — rule-validated wave counting that admits when there is no count[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Most auto-Elliott tools label every swing, whether the result is a legal wave count or not. Elliott Wave Radar takes the opposite approach: it builds ZigZag pivots, tests every possible interpretation against the hard Elliott Wave rules, scores the survivors by Fibonacci guideline adherence (0–100), and only draws a count when one actually qualifies. When nothing qualifies, the dashboard says "No valid count" — no forced labels.

[b]Hard rules enforced[/b]
[list]
[*]Wave 2 never retraces beyond the start of Wave 1
[*]Wave 3 is never the shortest of waves 1, 3 and 5
[*]Wave 4 never enters Wave 1 price territory (optional diagonal mode relaxes this)
[*]Wave 3 must exceed the end of Wave 1, Wave 5 the end of Wave 3
[/list]

[b]Scoring (0–100)[/b]
[list]
[*]W2 retrace close to 0.5–0.618 of W1
[*]W3 extension close to 1.618 (or 2.618) of W1
[*]W4 retrace close to 0.382 of W3
[*]W5 close to 0.618–1.0 of W1
[*]Alternation bonus when W2 and W4 differ in depth
[/list]
A configurable score gate (default 55) filters mediocre counts.

[b]Corrections[/b]
[list]
[*]Zigzag A-B-C (B retraces 0.236–0.886 of A, C travels beyond A)
[*]Flat — regular and expanded (B retraces 0.90–1.38 of A)
[*]C-wave setup: after a completed impulse plus confirmed A-B, C targets are projected at 1.0 / 1.618 × A — with the impulse extreme as monitored invalidation
[/list]

[b]Developing counts and projections[/b]
[list]
[*]After W1–W2 confirm: Wave-3 setup with targets at 1.0 / 1.618 / 2.618 × W1
[*]After W1–W4 confirm: Wave-5 setup with targets at 0.618 / 1.0 / 1.618 × W1
[*]After a complete impulse: correction targets at 38.2 / 50 / 61.8 %
[*]Invalidation level drawn and monitored bar-by-bar — if price breaks it, the count is removed and an alert fires
[/list]

[b]Sub-wave verification[/b]
A second, finer pivot degree checks whether Wave 1 and Wave 3 internally divide into five legs. The result is labeled on the chart ((i)–(iv)) and summarized in the dashboard.

[b]Dashboard[/b]
Current count and direction, score, invalidation level, sub-structure check, and the runner-up interpretation (alt count).

[b]Alerts[/b]
Impulse complete · A-B-C complete · Flat complete · C-wave setup · Wave-3 setup · Wave-5 setup · count invalidated.

[b]Honest limitations[/b]
Counts use confirmed pivots only (labels appear with the pivot confirmation delay — no repainting, no real-time extreme calls). Only the most recent structure is labeled, one degree is counted, and triangles/complex corrections (W-X-Y) are not modeled — such phases show "No valid count".

